  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the wood-fired oven to 220°C (425°F).",
    "In a large bowl, mix together the galangal-kha, ground beef, onion, garlic, salt, and black pepper until just combined.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a baking dish and drizzle with olive oil.",
    "Spread the chimichurri sauce evenly over the top of the mixture.",
    "Bake for 25 minutes, or until the top is golden brown and the internal temperature reaches 71°C (160°F).",
    "Sprinkle with fresh parsley and serve hot.",
    "Let the dish rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
    "Serve warm and enjoy!"
